Class StartReturn

java.lang.Object
  om.qengine.StartReturn

public class StartReturn
extends java.lang.Object

Returned data from OmService.start(String,String,String,String[],String[],String[]) call. Wraps information from Rendering.

API CLASS: This class is used in SOAP returns and should probably not be altered (after initial release).

getQuestionSession

public java.lang.String getQuestionSession()
Returns:
Question session ID. (Not a user session ID! Used to refer to the period between a start() call and the end of the question or stop().)

getXHTML

public java.lang.String getXHTML()
Obtains XHTML content. XHTML content must:
  • Be well-formed, with single root element
  • Be suitable for placing within <body>
  • Not use named entities except the basic XML set.
The following placeholder strings may be included in the content and will be replaced by the test navigator:
PlaceholderReplacement
%%RESOURCE%%Path [relative or absolute] at which resources will become available. This should not include the terminating /.
Example: If a resource has the name myfile.png, then <img src="%%RESOURCES%%/myfile.png"/> should work to include that image.
%%IDPREFIX%%must be put at the start of all id and name attributes in the XHTML (and references to them in Javascript.

Returns:
XHTML content as string.

CSS file. Null if none is required.

getProgressInfo

public java.lang.String getProgressInfo()
Returns:
Short textual information of progress on question, which should be displayed alongside the question. (For example, this might indicate how many attempts at the question are remaining.) Null indicates no change from previously-returned info (or blank if this is the first time).
